                    TXYBER BUSINESS EMAIL EXTRACTOR
                         User Guide - Version 1.9.2
================================================================================

Turn map listings into export-ready business email lists — locally, privately,
on your terms.

Website:    https://txyber.com
Help file:  datascraper map\help.html
Privacy:    datascraper map\privacy.html


================================================================================
WHAT THIS EXTENSION DOES
================================================================================

Txyber Business Email Extractor is a Chrome extension for sales, marketing,
and outreach teams. It collects PUBLIC business contact data from map search
results. Your data stays on your computer — it is not sent to the cloud.

Main features:

  - Works while you browse business listings on Google Maps
  - Finds published emails from public business websites (optional)
  - Shows a live dashboard with lead counts and unique emails
  - Export to CSV, TXT, or XLSX — all saved locally in your browser
  - Optional website access — you choose when to allow it
  - Powered by Txyber (https://txyber.com)

IMPORTANT DISCLAIMER:
This extension is NOT affiliated with, endorsed by, or sponsored by Google.
Google Maps is a trademark of Google LLC.
Use only on public business data you are legally allowed to collect.


================================================================================
HOW TO INSTALL
================================================================================

STEP 1 — Find the correct folder

After you download or unzip the project, open this folder:

  datascraper map LATEST
      └── datascraper map     <-- SELECT THIS FOLDER

Inside "datascraper map" you should see manifest.json, popup.html,
dashboard.html, and an icons folder.


STEP 2 — Load in Chrome

  1. Open Chrome and type in the address bar:  chrome://extensions/
  2. Turn ON "Developer mode" (switch at the top right)
  3. Click "Load unpacked"
  4. Select the "datascraper map" folder (the one with manifest.json)


STEP 3 — Pin the extension

  1. Click the puzzle piece icon in Chrome's toolbar
  2. Find "Txyber Business Email Extractor"
  3. Click the pin icon so it stays visible


================================================================================
HOW TO USE — STEP BY STEP
================================================================================

STEP 1 — Open the popup

  Click the Txyber icon in your Chrome toolbar.

  You will see:
    - A search box for your map query
    - "Open Maps" button
    - "Enable website access" button (optional)
    - Links to Dashboard, Privacy, and Help


STEP 2 — Start a map search

  1. Type a search, for example:  coffee shop near new york
  2. Click "Open Maps"
  3. Google Maps opens with your search results


STEP 3 — Extract business listings

  On the Google Maps page, look for the Txyber floating panel.

  1. Click "Start Auto Extract"
  2. Watch the "Leads" number go up as listings are collected
  3. Click "Stop Auto Extract" when you have enough results


STEP 4 — Find emails (optional)

  To discover emails from public business websites:

  1. Open the extension popup again
  2. Click "Enable website access"
  3. Click Allow when Chrome asks for permission

  Note: This is optional. It only visits public business websites linked
  from the map listings — not random pages on the internet.


STEP 5 — Review and export your data

  1. In the popup, click "Open results dashboard"
  2. Review your table (names, phones, addresses, websites, emails)
  3. Click one of the export buttons:

       Email CSV  — clean list of emails only (CSV format)
       Email TXT  — one email address per line
       Full CSV   — all collected columns
       Full XLSX  — full data in Excel format

  All files are created on your computer. Nothing is uploaded to Txyber.


