================================================================================
PERMISSIONS EXPLAINED
================================================================================

Storage
  Saves your collected leads inside your browser only.

Website access (optional)
  Lets the extension visit public business websites from listings to find
  published email addresses. You must click to enable this.

Google Maps access
  Shows the extract buttons only on Google Maps search pages.

Your lead lists are NOT uploaded to Txyber servers.
Full details: datascraper map\privacy.html


================================================================================
TROUBLESHOOTING
================================================================================

Problem: "Failed to load extension" or manifest error

  Fix:
    - Load the "datascraper map" folder, NOT the parent folder
    - Make sure manifest.json is inside the folder you select
    - Use the latest version of the extension files


Problem: Extract button does not appear on Maps

  Fix:
    - Refresh the Google Maps tab
    - Make sure you are on a Maps search page (URL contains /maps/)
    - Check the extension is turned on at chrome://extensions/


Problem: No emails found

  Fix:
    - Click "Enable website access" in the popup
    - Make sure the business listing has a website link
    - Some businesses do not publish emails online — that is normal


